# Domain Layer Purity

The domain is the innermost ring. It must remain **framework-agnostic and I/O-free**.

## Forbidden Imports in `domain/`

| Category | Examples |
|----------|----------|
| Web frameworks | `fastapi`, `starlette`, `flask`, `django` |
| ORM / DB | `sqlalchemy`, `asyncpg`, `psycopg2`, raw SQL strings |
| Computer vision / ML | `cv2` (OpenCV), `paddleocr`, `ultralytics`, `torch`, `onnxruntime` |
| HTTP clients | `httpx`, `requests`, `aiohttp` |
| Config / env | `os.environ`, `pydantic_settings` (use ports in application layer) |
| Infrastructure | Any import from `infrastructure/`, `interfaces/` |

## Allowed

- Python standard library (pure: `dataclasses`, `enum`, `datetime`, `uuid`, `typing`)
- Other `domain/` modules (prefer `domain/common/` shared kernel — keep it small)
- `application/` — **never** (dependency points inward only)

## Domain Artifacts

| Type | Location | Example |
|------|----------|---------|
| Entity | `entities/` | `Capture`, `VerificationOutcome` |
| Value object | `value_objects/` | `PlateNumber`, `ConfidenceScore` |
| Domain service | `services/` | `CloneDetectionPolicy`, `DecisionPolicy` |
| Domain exception | `exceptions/` | `InvalidPlateFormatError` |
| Domain event | `events/` | `PlateVerified`, `CloneSuspected` |

## PlateNumber Example (conceptual)

Normalization rules (strip spaces, uppercase, jurisdiction format) live in `PlateNumber` VO — not in OCR adapter or HTTP handler.

## Review Checklist

- [ ] No `import` from outer layers
- [ ] No file I/O, network, or database calls
- [ ] Business rules testable with zero mocks
